'''Geta''' is a [[municipalities of Finland|municipality]] of [[Åland]], an autonomous territory of [[Finland]]. The municipality has a population of {{formatnum: {{Infobox Finnish Municipality/population count|{{PAGENAME}}}}}} ({{#time: j F Y|{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/population count|sourcedate}} }})<ref name="population_count" /> and covers an area of {{convert|{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/total area|{{PAGENAME}}}}|km2}} of which {{convert|{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/waters area|{{PAGENAME}}}}|km2|abbr=on}} is water.<ref name="total_area" /> The [[population density]] is {{convert|{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/population density|{{PAGENAME}}|round=2}}|PD/km2}}. The municipality is unilingually [[Swedish language|Swedish]]. ==References== {{reflist}} ==External links== {{commonscat-inline|Geta}} *[http://www.geta.ax/ Municipality of Geta] – Official website [[File:Soltuna i Geta, norra Åland (december 1990)..jpg|thumb|left|260px|Soltuna, Geta]] {{Municipalities of Åland}} [[Category:Municipalities of Åland]] {{Åland-geo-stub}}
